==生理問題==
科學家表示航天活動期間的各種生理變化可能會影響人類的性和生殖。該些變化是由重力、辐射、噪音、振动、昼夜节律紊乱、压力等等多方面因素引起的<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Reproduction in the Space Environment: Part II. Concerns for Human Reproduction|url=http://journals.lww.com/00006254-199001000-00006|last=Jennings|first=Richard T.|last2=Santy|first2=PATRlClA A.|date=1990-01|journal=Obstetrical & Gynecological Survey|issue=1|doi=10.1097/00006254-199001000-00006|volume=45|pages=7–17|language=en|issn=0029-7828}}</ref>。

===重力和微重力===
在地球以外進行繁殖的挑战之一在於重力加速度欠奉。地球上的生物都是在重力場1[[G力|g]]的情況下進行繁殖和演化。因此若要在外太空進行繁殖，那麼就必須先研究它會怎樣影響哺乳動物的繁殖、宮內發育、受精、懷孕、出生、產後發育、成長照料<ref name="Ronca2003">{{Cite book|chapter=Mammalian Development in Space|title=Advances in Space Biology and Medicine|url=https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S1569257403090099|publisher=Elsevier|date=2003|isbn=978-0-444-51353-3|pages=217–251|volume=9|doi=10.1016/s1569-2574(03)09009-9|language=en|first=April E|last=Ronca|access-date=2021-08-23|archive-date=2018-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180629225905/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S1569257403090099|dead-url=no}}</ref>。重力會影響脊椎动物的细胞结构和功能、器官发展、行為，繼而影響发育。此外它還會影響哺乳动物的基因表達，故此若要在地外环境進行繁殖，重力便成了不可忽略的因素。

研究者已研究了實驗動物在微重力狀態下怎樣繁殖。一項研究觀察了[[实验大鼠|大鼠]]的有關過程。结果顯示，儘管大鼠胎兒在正常重力下發展，但一旦把已出娘胎的大鼠放到微重力環境中成長，那麼其糾錯能力便會變弱<ref>{{cite web|title=Utricular and saccular projections of fetal rats raised in normal gravity and microgravity|url=http://gateway.nlm.nih.gov/MeetingAbstracts/ma?f=102222743.html|accessdate=2014-01-25|date=October 1995|last=B|first=Fritzsch|website=NLM Gateway Search|publisher=ASGSB Bull|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809060317/http://gateway.nlm.nih.gov/MeetingAbstracts/ma?f=102222743.html|archivedate=2011-08-09|first2=Bruce|last2=LL|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另一項研究則觀察了小鼠在微重力下的受精情況。結果發現，雖然在正常重力和微重力環境中誕生的小鼠，都能在正常重力環境下健康成長，但微重力環境下的受精率比起正常重力為低<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Detrimental Effects of Microgravity on Mouse Preimplantation Development In Vitro|url=https://dx.plos.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0006753|last=Wakayama|first=Sayaka|last2=Kawahara|first2=Yumi|date=2009-08-25|journal=PLoS ONE|issue=8|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0006753|editor-last=Dey|editor-first=Sudhansu Kumar|volume=4|pages=e6753|language=en|issn=1932-6203|pmc=PMC2727478|pmid=19707597|last3=Li|first3=Chong|last4=Yamagata|first4=Kazuo|last5=Yuge|first5=Louis|last6=Wakayama|first6=Teruhiko}}</ref>。目前還沒有小鼠或大鼠在微重力環境下渡過整個生命週期的研究記錄<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Effects of microgravity on cell cytoskeleton and embryogenesis|url=http://www.intjdevbiol.com/paper.php?doi=052077sc|last=Crawford-Young|first=Susan J.|date=2006|journal=The International Journal of Developmental Biology|issue=2-3|doi=10.1387/ijdb.052077sc|volume=50|pages=183–191|language=en|issn=0214-6282|pmid=16479487|access-date=2021-08-23|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821142143/http://www.intjdevbiol.com/paper.php?doi=052077sc|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===雙人套裝===
{{le|雙人套裝|2suit}}是一款經過特別設計的服裝，其能夠讓人更易在失重或低重力環境下進行低強度的性行為<ref name="vanna">{{cite web|title=Vanna Bonta Talks Sex in Space|url=http://www.femail.com.au/vanna-bonta-talks-sex-in-space.htm|accessdate=2015-06-12|date=2012-08-19|website=Femail.com.au|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150322102732/http://www.femail.com.au/vanna-bonta-talks-sex-in-space.htm|archivedate=2015-03-22|deadurl=no}}</ref>。它由美国小说家{{link-en|范娜·邦塔|Vanna Bonta}}发明<ref name="msnbc"/>，及後成為了[[歷史頻道|歷史頻道]]記錄片《太空中的性愛》（2008年）的探討主題。該部記錄片講述若人类在外太空遷徙和繁衍，那麽會為其帶來怎樣的影響<ref name="vanna"/><ref>{{Cite episode|title=Sex in Space|series=The Universe|network=[[歷史頻道|History Channel]]|date=2008-12-02|season=3}}</ref><ref>[https://www.newscientist.com/blogs/shortsharpscience/2008/12/history-channel-to-air-special.html History Channel to air special on 'sex in space'] {{Wayback|url=https://www.newscientist.com/blogs/shortsharpscience/2008/12/history-channel-to-air-special.html |date=20160915155939 }} New Scientist 2008-12-17</ref>。雙人套裝的誕生引發了一輪有關太空殖民的爭論<ref name="thelmagazine">{{Cite web|title=Celebrate Sputnik Day by Thinking About Space Sex|url=https://www.thelmagazine.com/2012/10/celebrate-sputnik-day-by-thinking-about-space-sex/|access-date=2021-08-23|date=2012-10-04|work=The L Magazine|language=en-US|archive-date=2015-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612200151/http://www.thelmagazine.com/2012/10/celebrate-sputnik-day-by-thinking-about-space-sex/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="thepaltrysapien.com">{{cite web|title=1000 Words, 1000 Days: Day 351 – Space-Boinking In The 21st Century!|url=http://www.thepaltrysapien.com/2012/12/1000-words-1000-days-day-351-space-boinking-in-the-21st-century/|date=2012-12-16|last=Schwartz|first=Marty|website=The Paltry Sapien|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141110233101/http://www.thepaltrysapien.com/2012/12/1000-words-1000-days-day-351-space-boinking-in-the-21st-century/|archivedate=2014-11-10|access-date=2020-10-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

